    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is compensated by multi-laboratory replication, tight inter-laboratory agreement, and the fact that ASTM F1717 specifies a single standardized test configuration. All three QoIs pass both the <10% difference and E/uval < 1.96 acceptance criteria. The overall evidence package is judged sufficient to support a Medium assurance level determination for this COU.",
